{"id":2575,"date":"2012-03-29T06:39:05","date_gmt":"2012-03-29T02:39:05","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=2575"},"modified":"2023-08-28T17:03:17","modified_gmt":"2023-08-28T13:03:17","slug":"seek-refuge-after-prayer","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/03\/29\/seek-refuge-after-prayer\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dua: Supplication for refuge at the end of prayer"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>When one of you finishes his testimony at the end of prayer, let him seek refuge in Allah from four trials, saying: O Allah, I seek refuge in You from the punishment of Hell, from the punishment of the grave, from the trials of life and death, and from the evil trial of the False Messiah<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 588<\/p>\n<p>Grade:<b><i> Sahih <\/i><\/b>(authentic) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650<\/span> <span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">\u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e<\/span> <span s